"[\n  \"BREAKING: French Interior Ministry confirms 14 fatalities at Charlie Hebdo HQ, including editor Stéphane Charbonnier. Shooter identified as Algerian national.\",\n  \"Official Update: Paris Police Prefecture reports three suspects in custody following the raid on Rue Nicolas-Appert. All hostages secured safely.\",\n  \"Confirmed: The attack was coordinated by ISIS cell leader Abu Bakr al-Baghdadi via encrypted channel at 10:15 AM CET. Source: DGSI internal memo.\",\n  \"Just in: Charlie Hebdo offices evacuated due to second bomb threat. Police found 2kg of TNT in the basement. No casualties reported in this incident.\",\n  \"Update from Elysée Palace: President Hollande declares national mourning. State funeral for victims scheduled for Friday at Notre-Dame Cathedral.\",\n  \"Verified: Two police officers killed in crossfire near Boulevard Richard-Lenoir. Suspects fled in a black Citroën C3, license plate 75-AB-92.\",\n  \"Charlie Hebdo legal team confirms publication of next issue will be delayed indefinitely due to structural damage to the printing press in Pantin.\",\n  \"DGSE report leaks: Attackers were trained in Yemen camp in 2013. Funds traced to Qatari charity account ending in 8842. Investigation ongoing.\",\n  \"Paris Hospital Group AP-HP confirms 5 critical patients in stable condition at Hôpital Saint-Antoine. Blood donations urgently needed at site B.\",\n  \"Official statement: The cartoonist known as 'Cabu' survived the initial volley but succumbed to injuries at 11:45 AM. Family requests privacy.\",\n  \"Counter-terrorism unit neutralized third accomplice in Monrouge. Body found with detonator vest. Area within 500m radius cordoned off until 18:00.\",\n  \"Ministry of Culture announces emergency grant of €5 million to Charlie Hebdo for rebuilding. Editorial board to relocate to Lyon headquarters temporarily.\"\n]"